When converting the AOE radius into a decal size in FVector, the main factor to take into consideration is the aspect ratio of the decal's texture. Here's how you can convert the AOE radius to a decal size:

1. Determine the decal texture aspect ratio: Open the decal material in Unreal Engine's Material Editor and find the texture used for the decal. Note the dimensions of the texture (width and height). Calculate the aspect ratio as follows: `AspectRatio = TextureWidth / TextureHeight`.

2. Calculate the decal size based on the AOE radius: Multiply the AOE radius by 2 to get the diameter. Then, multiply the aspect ratio by the diameter to obtain the length of the decal along the X-axis. The diameter itself will be the length along the Y-axis, and you can decide the thickness along the Z-axis based on your requirements. The decal size will be represented as FVector: `FVector(AOEDiameter * AspectRatio, AOEDiameter, Thickness)`.

Here's a code example demonstrating this:

```cpp
// Assuming you have the AOE Radius and AspectRatio
float AOERadius = 300.0f;
float AspectRatio = 1.0f; // Assuming a square texture, replace with your texture's aspect ratio

float AOEDiameter = AOERadius * 2.0f;
float DecalThickness = 1.0f; // Set the value based on your requirement

FVector DecalSize = FVector(AOEDiameter * AspectRatio, AOEDiameter, DecalThickness);

// Set the decal size to the Decal Component
AOEDecal->DecalSize = DecalSize;
```

